The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC, on Election Day intercepted bags of money suspected to be ferried to various locations across the state for vote-buying at North Bank Area, Makurdi, Benue State.
EFCC in a tweet indicated that its operatives were on patrol when they intercepted some individuals carrying the alleged bags of cash.
“In an attempt to arrest the culprit, some thugs attacked operatives and vandalised the bus used for patrol. #SayNoToVoteBuying”, the tweet read.
